Notore Chemicals Plc said it has secured N13.320 billion loan facility from African Export-Import Bank (Afreximbank) for equipment maintenance. The company in a statement signed by the company secretary, Mrs Otivbo Saleh said that the loan was secured from the African Export-Import Bank for the planned turnaround maintenance. It announced the commencement of the TAM of its plant, which it said was aimed at returning the plant to its 1,500MTPD and 500,000MTPA nameplate urea production capacity, saying that it would also increase reliability index from the current level of 67 per cent to 95 per cent. According to the statement, following the drawdown of the N13.32 billion loan facility from Afreximbank, the company has started ordering all key components for the maintenance. “The TAM project would include the procurement of critical spare parts required to sustain the nameplate capacity of the plant and installation of a back-up power supply to the current gas turbine generator. “Upon procurement of all the key components and critical spares required, the objective is to accomplish the maintenance activities within a period of 30-day production to production.” As part of measures to return the group and the company to profitability and improve working capital, the management said it would embark on a TAM of its production plant and equipment to improve its reliability and increase production output. The TAM programme, it said at the time, would be funded by a seven year tenured loan of $37 million to be obtained from the African Export-Import Bank. The company in its audited result released recently for the period ended September 30, 2019 showed a Group revenue of N21.42 billion as against N26.82 billion in 2018, cost of sales stood at N17.45 billion, higher than N17.22 achieved in 2018, while gross profit for the profit declined to N3.96 billion lower than N9.61 billion recorded for 2018. Also, the group recorded net losses of N5.75 billion during the year ended September 30, 2019 and the net current liabilities as of that date were N37.03 billion. Notore Chemical Industries Plc was incorporated in Nigeria on November 30, 2005, as a private limited liability company, and is domiciled in Nigeria. Its registered office address is Notore Industrial Complex, Onne, River State, Nigeria. On June 13, 2014, the company was re-registered as a public limited liability company and was listed on the Main Board of the Nigerian Stock Exchange on August 2, 2018.